{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, u ̸ ∈ {y ∈ S ′ | R ′ i (y) ⊆ ↓ X}, so there is a z ∈ R ′ i (u) with z ̸ ⊑ X, so for some x ∈ X, z ̸ ⊑ x and hence z ∧ -x ̸ = ⊥.",
    "Given uR ′ i z, z ∧ -x ̸ = ⊥, and u ⊑ i x, by R-rule from Proposition 4.42 there is a v ∈ S ′ with i xR ′ i v and v ∧ -x ̸ = ⊥.",
    "But i x = max{y ∈ S ′ | R ′ i (y) ⊆ ↓x}, so i xR ′ i v implies v ⊑ x, contradicting v ∧ -x ̸ = ⊥.For part 4, it suffices to show that F ′ is a T -BAO.",
    "Since F is quasifunctional, F ⊥ is an extended quasi-functional frame (recall Definition 4.25), so for every z ∈ S ′, there is anf ′ i (z) ∈ S ′ such that f ′ i (z) = max(R ′ i (z)).",
    "We must show that y ⊑ ′ i x iff f ′ i (y) ⊑ x."
